T*
(3\) How Auth Is Handled) Tj
T*
(============================================================) Tj
T*
(Auth strategy in this codebase:) Tj
T*
(- JWT-based auth.) Tj
T*
(- Frontend stores JWT and user object in localStorage keys: token, user.) Tj
T*
(- Axios request interceptor reads localStorage token and sends:) Tj
T*
(  Authorization: Bearer <token>) Tj
T*
(- Backend protect middleware reads token only from Authorization header and verifies with ) Tj
T*
(JWT_SECRET.) Tj
T*
(- 401 response interceptor clears localStorage token/user and redirects to /login?expired=1.) Tj
T*
(- Cookie-based session/JWT auth is NOT implemented in middleware.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Google OAuth path:) Tj
T*
(- Backend Google callback issues JWT and redirects to frontend with token + user in query params.) Tj
T*
(- Frontend GoogleAuthSuccess page reads params and calls AuthContext login\(\), which persists to ) Tj
T*
(localStorage.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
